{"action": "input", "code": "def find_gray_area(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing a grid and returns the value of the area surrounded by gray.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing a grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the value of the area surrounded by gray.\n    \"\"\"\n    gray_indices = np.where(input_grid == grey)\n    gray_area = len(set(zip(gray_indices[0], gray_indices[1])))\n    return gray_area\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    value = find_gray_area(input_grid)\n    out = change_pattern_color(input_grid, value)\n    return out\ndef change_pattern_color(input_grid: np.ndarray, value: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing a grid and an integer value and changes the color of the pattern\n    with the same shape as the pattern in the gray box to the input value.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing a grid.\n    value: An integer representing the new color value.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    gray_indices = np.where(input_grid == grey)\n    gray_rows, gray_cols = (gray_indices[0], gray_indices[1])\n    pattern_rows = max(gray_rows) - min(gray_rows) + 1\n    pattern_cols = max(gray_cols) - min(gray_cols) + 1\n    pattern = input_grid[min(gray_rows):max(gray_rows) + 1, min(gray_cols):max(gray_cols) + 1]\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0] - pattern_rows + 1):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1] - pattern_cols + 1):\n            if np.array_equal(input_grid[i:i + pattern_rows, j:j + pattern_cols], pattern):\n                input_grid[i:i + pattern_rows, j:j + pattern_cols] = value\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    value = `Find the value of the area surrounded by gray.`(input_grid)\n    out = `Change the color of the pattern with the same shape as the pattern in the gray box to input value`(input_grid,value)\n    return out\n", "gpt_code": "def find_gray_area(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing a grid and returns the value of the area surrounded by gray.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing a grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the value of the area surrounded by gray.\n    \"\"\"\n    gray_indices = np.where(input_grid == grey)\n    gray_area = len(set(zip(gray_indices[0], gray_indices[1])))\n    return gray_area\ndef change_pattern_color(input_grid: np.ndarray, value: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing a grid and an integer value and changes the color of the pattern\n    with the same shape as the pattern in the gray box to the input value.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing a grid.\n    value: An integer representing the new color value.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    gray_indices = np.where(input_grid == grey)\n    gray_rows, gray_cols = (gray_indices[0], gray_indices[1])\n    pattern_rows = max(gray_rows) - min(gray_rows) + 1\n    pattern_cols = max(gray_cols) - min(gray_cols) + 1\n    pattern = input_grid[min(gray_rows):max(gray_rows) + 1, min(gray_cols):max(gray_cols) + 1]\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0] - pattern_rows + 1):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1] - pattern_cols + 1):\n            if np.array_equal(input_grid[i:i + pattern_rows, j:j + pattern_cols], pattern):\n                input_grid[i:i + pattern_rows, j:j + pattern_cols] = value\n    return input_grid", "holes": {"find_gray_area": "Find the value of the area surrounded by gray.", "change_pattern_color": "Change the color of the pattern with the same shape as the pattern in the gray box to input value"}}
